Um, some of the, you know, budgets picture, um, a couple of months ago when it was even less clear than it is now.

663
01:07:47,937 --> 01:08:03,560
Um, but under the city form of government, if the school committee's role, while there is a vote in the statutory required, statutory required vote to adopt the budget, um, that is ultimately appropriated by the municipal government.

664
01:08:03,980 --> 01:08:06,841
If the question is what happens if the school committee

665
01:08:08,063 --> 01:08:19,974
refuses to vote to adopt the budget that the municipal government appropriated, then there really isn't a specific sort of how-to with regard to that.

666
01:08:20,254 --> 01:08:27,580
The administration would be in a position where the governing body that we report to has not approved spending for fiscal year 22.

667
01:08:28,441 --> 01:08:35,828
We would then consult with the Department of Revenue and get guidance as to how we should proceed.

668
01:08:36,900 --> 01:08:45,988
I think you can expect what you would typically see in a situation in which there's, functionally speaking, a government shutdown.

669
01:08:46,488 --> 01:08:59,759
It's not common at all, again, in a municipal structure like we have in the city of Medford, because there isn't really a good offering at that point.

670
01:09:00,419 --> 01:09:05,183
So the committee's role is in making the initial request to the municipal government

671
01:09:05,869 --> 01:09:11,332
um, articulating and really it's the administration's responsibility to make sure that we're articulating a defense to that.

672
01:09:11,932 --> 01:09:12,632
Uh, request.

673
01:09:12,792 --> 01:09:18,875
And then the municipal government ultimately makes is, is the, is the spending branch of the municipal government.

674
01:09:18,935 --> 01:09:21,196
And ultimately that's the appropriation that's going to be made.

675
01:09:21,676 --> 01:09:31,741
I think the reason that there isn't clear guidance spelled out today is because if the school committee were to refuse to accept the budget that was allocated from the municipal government.

676
01:09:32,277 --> 01:09:35,638
there wouldn't be sort of a plan B for the school department.

677
01:09:35,838 --> 01:09:43,239
The municipal government ultimately would, you know, could decide, you know, how it was going to respond to that.

