01:19:56,713 --> 01:20:03,214
I need to actually have an answer to what happens if we refuse to approve a budget that we don't feel is adequate.

780
01:20:04,535 --> 01:20:10,096
And I don't wanna find out after we are there, what the consequences are.

781
01:20:10,116 --> 01:20:11,597
I think we need an answer.

782
01:20:13,019 --> 01:20:16,120
The, you know, several members last year were like, well, what will happen?

783
01:20:16,520 --> 01:20:20,702
And here we are coming up on another year where several of us are asking what will happen.

784
01:20:21,222 --> 01:20:24,743
And I can't believe that in Massachusetts with 351 communities.

785
01:20:24,823 --> 01:20:29,605
And I know there's very different forms of government that nobody has ever refused to pass a budget.

786
01:20:29,625 --> 01:20:31,445
That just doesn't seem plausible.

787
01:20:32,406 --> 01:20:33,066
So just be clear.

788
01:20:33,146 --> 01:20:34,746
It doesn't seem like it's there.

789
01:20:34,907 --> 01:20:35,407
Absolutely.

790
01:20:35,527 --> 01:20:38,528
The school committees that are refused to adopt the budget.

791
01:20:39,048 --> 01:20:39,208
Okay.

792
01:20:39,635 --> 01:20:43,856
And I'm happy to seek outside counsel and provide you with a legal opinion.

793
01:20:44,136 --> 01:20:46,076
I will say, I am an attorney that's done this.

794
01:20:46,176 --> 01:20:48,477
I have talked to other attorneys that have dealt with this.

795
01:20:48,817 --> 01:20:56,419
And the issue is that in this form of government, with this timing, it is so nonsensical that there isn't a clear path forward.

796
01:20:56,699 --> 01:21:02,980
There are various options, some of which I think are of questionable legality, but there are absolutely paths forward at that point.

797
01:21:03,400 --> 01:21:07,721
In some of the other forms of government, there are contingencies that are built in

798
01:21:08,302 --> 01:21:10,404
And there are levers that can then be adopted.

799
01:21:10,604 --> 01:21:12,645
In this form of government, there aren't as many.

800
01:21:12,745 --> 01:21:18,810
So there aren't gonna be, there will not be a good option available, but that's not to suggest that there will be no options.

801
01:21:19,210 --> 01:21:25,575
And I really, really wanna be clear that there are two points in the budget sequence here.

