804
01:21:38,560 --> 01:21:49,669
But that is a different question than whether the administration who works for the school committee can legally spend money if no vote has been adopted.

805
01:21:49,809 --> 01:21:59,357
I will tell you that in a lot of school committees, and this is sort of the ugly truth of school governance, they often forget to take the second vote.

806
01:21:59,577 --> 01:22:00,658
That is not uncommon.

807
01:22:00,918 --> 01:22:04,681
And I think the school committee association probably is more familiar with this than I am.

808
01:22:05,082 --> 01:22:06,523
But once the request is made,

809
01:22:06,933 --> 01:22:14,577
and the municipal government ultimately makes that appropriation, most school committees just consider their previous vote to have been their approval of the budget.

810
01:22:14,917 --> 01:22:25,022
And then administratively, the funding flows in and people get paid and off we go throughout the course of the fiscal year and we live happily ever after, okay?

811
01:22:25,182 --> 01:22:32,385
There is a statute that makes it very clear that there's an expectation that the committee adopt a budget after that appropriation is made.

812
01:22:33,086 --> 01:22:35,427
And I think it would be a best practice to follow that

813
01:22:36,042 --> 01:22:44,984
And I don't think it would be the best practice to not expend the funding that was appropriate, especially when you are in no way closed off from continuing to advocate.

814
01:22:45,324 --> 01:22:54,025
I understand there could be some symbolic value in just saying no, but I don't think there's any legal or strategic value in that.

815
01:22:54,625 --> 01:23:05,667
And again, if the idea is you have complete control over where the money is spent, because there's an absolute prohibition on the municipal government telling the school committee how to spend within the eligible expenses,

816
01:23:06,445 --> 01:23:19,548
you, it seems to me that the more prudent strategy would be that adopted money, especially when there's a two month runway before most students are even in the buildings and then continue to advocate for a supplemental budget.

817
01:23:19,728 --> 01:23:33,912
